headline: United States Spice (Pure, Blended) Market Analysis Report 2025-2033: Rising Demand for Natural Ingredients, Culinary Diversity, and Global Cuisine Influence Across Multicultural States
summary: The United States spice market is set to surge from US$ 9.19 billion in 2024 to US$ 15.8 billion by 2033, at a CAGR of 6.21%. Key drivers include the rising preference for natural ingredients, cultural diversity, and global cuisine influence on American food choices. Demand for organic and health-promoting spices like turmeric and ginger, bolstered by e-commerce growth, fuels this trend. Challenges such as supply chain disruptions and quality control persist. headline: JELL-O Revives Its 125-Year-Old Iconic Thanksgiving Molds for the First Time
summary: PITTSBURGH & CHICAGO, November 10, 2025--For more than a century, JELL-O molds have held a special place on America’s holiday tables, becoming one of the most recognizable traditions of the season. While Thanksgiving tables are full of love and gratitude there are always a few side dishes everyone expects - but not everyone likes. This year, JELL-O is offering a new colorful twist. headline: 1 S&P 500 Stock with Competitive Advantages and 2 We Turn Down
summary: The S&P 500 (^GSPC) is home to the biggest and most well-known companies in the market, making it a go-to index for investors seeking stability. But not all large-cap stocks are created equal - some are struggling with slowing growth, declining margins, or increased competition.
